[assistant] Fixed the failing `MimeUtilTest`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - `MimeBodyPart` construction needs a `jakarta.mail.util.StreamProvider`.
[assistant] - The Jakarta EE API artifact does not provide one by default in this test setup, so `MimeBodyPart` failed before reaching `MimeUtil`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made:
[assistant] - Updated `MimeUtilTest` to set `StreamProvider.class.getName()` to the existing `SessionTest.TestStreamProvider` before constructing `MimeBodyPart`.
[assistant] - The content type handler property and rejecting context class loader are now applied immediately before calling `part.getContentType()`, so the test still targets `MimeUtil`’s dynamic-access paths.
[assistant] 
