[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test coverage**\n\nI’m realizing we need to modify tests since the report shows only the fallback covered, not the context loader. It seems like the RejectingClassLoader might have caused an issue with Class.forName that threw a ClassNotFoundException. \n\nI’m considering that the MimeBodyPart construction might not trigger MimeUtil, and wait, did the property and loader get set before calling getContentType? There could be confusion due to initializing the class before setting the loader. A previous test might have set the property first, so my test might not be the first to run in the JVM. What a puzzle!\n\n**Refining test strategies**\n\nI’m considering whether to skip line 41 if the context loader is null and instead do line 45. It could be that in a Native image, the Thread's context loader is null, or maybe Class.forName with a custom loader isn’t supported. Since static initialization only happens once, I'm pondering if I need a separate test class to handle one-to-one mapping. \n\nThe issue is that I can't cover both scenarios in one JVM run since the MimeUtil already initializes. I wonder if I should refine the existing test to ensure line 41 is covered while maintaining coverage for line 45 in the future. I really want to make sure CI expects all areas to be tested, but dropping coverage isn’t a great option. This is quite the tricky situation!\n\n**Determining coverage strategies**\n\nI'm thinking about the rules for adding or refining tests to ensure coverage, especially for line 45, which might end up uncovered if not executed at all. The tricky part is that the iterative workflow seems to rely on previous progress, and the rules say we can't drop coverage.\n\nAn idea strikes me: could I launch isolated JVM subprocesses to test separately? Each could invoke the public API with different system properties while keeping the coverage agent in the parent. I need to balance this all carefully!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02d20df727719d4e016a01ee842ee0819cae6514432c238d8b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAe6Umyj7xM0LImiKGWbgwOIIyeXPKwupSdlrYG1nS9d2chshBTCHnlnI20fWUknAYUaKmQHg1TWKrMCORTx2tz_OMhBW6I1XoRXErCH8B-DIE-R1_AyUR3cp7KGA5r79ca8Js3r7IJ4OXkL7qqdD1ngU2qqBEdaZvAUxiM3ea1Q9hGDK-weWS_WCiTgpRvkoBSJoSEnFB-3MfWoHxYo_OUKHT60Mge3jllTf448gLZMNOcSCatZtggCXpSaz_yFzSq-_Wula9yV4XVujd7iWwAb7T32jULJaBRvUxtbpgEB-OADJ1PlcVQYWJawdcVmzapMH98gP4wbS9qCUNNsKXRp4nmK6fNT9jmIxMqcCzxPe5KeA8qp6EmIb9jOopIR1Q03jE4iB02oA9yo_27YCjA4BulT_qbnR_LHcEiz7_xI-Ln-mQupeWVdq0pt6d5L-jb5o-lD4tKpHnKpfc2_letmMXgUpyYgmdqID_GMOWqwSlABHKIZUO4SiNhooCRZVvNgyaCq7lE4TiaZUJMW2j8Ui-95w89e5Xh0mZSXIQBAzPvhq24ms9IZI8dF9B2Mt2x0GJTxg0BtckQ3lKJTPLfsiI4rRXGg7Th63BpoOOvJr8rvcO6tvBynfz3_kcHLEHDnaEPV-wAorTgCLYbgTAR5IiryqjptcgBk4boUX0M44gNmA8TdSa-VKEnKMC-zga4LNGSgUf9lZUXu2J9sN75bMC5uxXvW3gX_qDq3jG6rmZJlnAbx7CDSsIYP1kwe6ZSNHYUCyUdLvX3DFmt3hFHZ38TWEMMYnctLhL-d0lhFg03z00kOY_8CohEEsYmU5PpZc9ILAEGjPRg6p1njxDf5GcTgUSs49sm5aRp0pm9XY_T9UUMUS5SCg264vD7JY4I1kOVulor9e3NNyzsAZIp9IsV0L8SBm26AMi5Po4_1HPn1BdbOHPFwiAH3LJzDjWB_WL3FxVUBmGbGAuWsmFdR3WZUEi7-aWIyjgIJ8nYbETvCDUZePhPX1jUMJM4-NmMvTb0lFowydq7_C3bJJ1YCzgPImYa_c9XVgjDDmobWhZuTElPZyzA1toHSdnBs1A5GoXhKEczMJCJMoyRSmczNYD2jyHA4aHEaN8Kfd_wKHjq-Qfkd9m2WByh5vo8G61-mF6rlVAgkfIDNEiIHX3uLOnGAt5sfjmSV4CtLZKlTqype2JzKEFNJVzOfrKu-dTURXWANPd5hw-LIQghRFcb0IhrkOkRw89WTvoJDjBXODRltwLvelprITsYOLn5JEuZHo7cGFA7esWat8B1sZIbMQkhdhwjnYcdc5twfCk9XSZyt4YQDbdmLBDBwVaO8hEzBJQBbG3YN-m1v-YQBxE-MgD5O1lLeJBms7Vg6VjfAWMqCQzMMV9WD5lInZW5IJGBX0-yrh2AZxDmJ7Sr8ydS8mR1h_VRGljviEdm5nWEXE0dM6uarEaMu32OYTCABNSgopJDzYK6H9WHjya0fo9ZKnXtNa39QbBkN96HVHnfufll1sHxLD3dU4eiVYGMED4nJEdm9gvHNt2LtStrx9JSa4Z946W_sNEWwZopY12l3xliAyEwVTk5jxzWfUnbDBBH317R_17Kwsi-qytSaw47GpfMijNLxXvKeEXnLBOMFBb1FpLi3Jgv1WEHy2lhyFiXyZWBNcYC-EKpjSCzNWsZIE2M_-vfXyePGNMYdbt6cmd027rzx-N7itEIo6Q4Svy_3GSVaLGWXAv_DTj-DZbd86cpIQ5fj9YqyLQiz4CCjkDxqm8a4FSpcWaQCGt7XmxRPEG