 one-to-one testing. \\n\\nI wonder if I could use JUnit’s @Isolated, but that doesn't seem right either. Perhaps I can achieve coverage for line 41 in one run and line 45 in another for cumulative reporting? So, the latest report indicates that line 41 is newly covered, but line 45 still needs work. Maybe I can switch the test back to the fallback option; does the system track cumulative coverage? Still, I need to ensure the final coverage run isn't missing line 41. The task emphasizes improving the active uncovered lines, so moving forward will require careful navigation through the harness’s cumulative progress.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring dynamic class loading**\\n\\nI’m thinking about dynamic class loading. I could try a bounded approach, but maybe it’s simpler to use a custom `ClassLoader` to load just `jakarta.mail.internet.MimeUtil`. However, since it’s package-private and calls the `MimePart` interface from the parent, it might work if they’re in the same package. I’d need to use reflection to invoke a public static method, but MimeUtil being package-private complicates things. It might be better to load the whole class and access `MimeBodyPart` through reflection. I’ll also need to find the jar path at runtime.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing handler implementation**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the fallback process where Class.forName finds a handler in the child class. That’s good to know! The handler method signature references the child MimePart because it's loaded by that class. I need to ensure the handler method uses only Strings and must be public, with no package visibility. Also, I should include URLs for both the library jar and the test classes directory in my setup.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IrUgZUAVmq2NPdX2c1pvQQax|fc_02d20df727719d4e016a01ef4d1c78819cb400cdd9b9373a31", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"NativeImageSupport|isUnsupportedFeatureError|URLClassLoader|Callable\" t